  "prompt": "Can I get my drivers license if I'm 17 in india?",
  "response": "Yes, you can get a driver's license if you're 17 years old in India, but there are specific conditions based on the type of vehicle you wish to drive. For a motorcycle with an engine capacity of 50 cc or less, you can apply for a learner's license at the age of 16. To get a permanent license for this category, you must hold the learner's license for at least 6 months.\n\nFor driving a non-geared motorcycle (scooter or moped) or a geared vehicle, such as a car or motorcycle with engine capacity more than 50 cc, the minimum age requirement is 18 years. Therefore, at 17, you wouldn't be eligible for a permanent driver's license for these types of vehicles yet.\n\nAdditionally, you will need to pass a driving test and meet other requirements such as submitting necessary documents, including proof of identity, age, and address. It\u2019s advisable to check with your local Regional Transport Office (RTO) for specific rules and regulations as they can vary slightly in different states.",
